EXPECTED VALUE CALCULATION:

üìä FINANCIAL BENEFITS (Quantifiable)

Cost Avoidance:
‚Ä¢ Rework reduction (15% ‚Üí 10%): $300K annual savings
  - BLS baseline: 15% of engineering budget
  - JMU evidence: 35% fewer failures with structured dissent
  - Conservative estimate: 5% reduction = $300K for $6M budget

‚Ä¢ Error prevention (48% communication-related): $200K annual savings
  - BLS: $22B industry-wide, 48% communication-caused
  - Mid-size org share: ~$200K preventable errors

‚Ä¢ Decision reversal reduction: $100K annual savings
  - McKinsey: 25-30% fewer costly reversals
  - Estimated 2-3 major reversals avoided per year

TOTAL FINANCIAL BENEFIT: $600K annually

üìà NON-FINANCIAL BENEFITS (High Value, Harder to Quantify)

Innovation Impact:
‚Ä¢ 20% more alternative solutions considered (McKinsey validation)
‚Ä¢ Earlier risk identification (pre-mortem effectiveness)
‚Ä¢ More innovative product features (Google: 30% higher innovation output)

Team Performance:
‚Ä¢ Higher psychological safety scores (Edmondson Scale improvement)
‚Ä¢ Increased employee engagement (Frazier: r=0.43 with learning behavior)
‚Ä¢ Reduced junior engineer attrition (feeling heard improves retention)

Decision Quality:
‚Ä¢ Better-informed strategic decisions (more diverse input)
‚Ä¢ Faster problem detection (anonymous reporting surfaces issues early)
‚Ä¢ Reduced organizational blind spots (groupthink symptoms diminished)

Reputation/Culture:
‚Ä¢ Reputation as high-performing, psychologically safe workplace
‚Ä¢ Attracts top talent seeking collaborative environments
‚Ä¢ Competitive advantage through better decision-making

üí∏ IMPLEMENTATION COSTS

One-Time Costs:
‚Ä¢ Manager training (facilitation, bias awareness): $10K-$20K
‚Ä¢ Anonymous tool subscriptions (Slido, SurveyMonkey): $500-$2K
‚Ä¢ Process design and documentation: $5K (internal effort)

TOTAL ONE-TIME: ~$20K

Ongoing Annual Costs:
‚Ä¢ Tool subscriptions: $2K/year
‚Ä¢ Quarterly manager refresher training: $5K/year
‚Ä¢ Facilitation time (embedded in meetings): No marginal cost

TOTAL ANNUAL: ~$7K

üìä ROI CALCULATION

Year 1:
‚Ä¢ Benefits: $600K
‚Ä¢ Costs: $20K (one-time) + $7K (annual) = $27K
‚Ä¢ NET VALUE: $573K
‚Ä¢ ROI: 2,122%

Years 2-5:
‚Ä¢ Annual Benefits: $600K
‚Ä¢ Annual Costs: $7K
‚Ä¢ NET ANNUAL VALUE: $593K

5-YEAR CUMULATIVE VALUE: $2.96M

EXPECTED VALUE SUMMARY:
Very high positive expected value ($573K net in year 1, $593K annually thereafter). ROI exceeds 2,000% in first year. Even with conservative 50% probability of achieving full benefits, expected value still exceeds $300K annually.</div>
